1
00:00:01,233 --> 00:00:03,200
<i>Roi Martinez. I've sent you
the profile of the suspect.</i>

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:04,733
<i> Block all the exits.</i>

3
00:00:04,733 --> 00:00:06,833
<i>That man can't leave
the island.</i>

4
00:00:06,833 --> 00:00:08,733
<i> We trusted him.</i>

5
00:00:08,733 --> 00:00:10,033
<i> That bastard!</i>

6
00:00:10,233 --> 00:00:13,200
<i> Kiko has a strong feeling
that Roi killed Papa.</i>

7
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:15,167
<i>He may be obsessed
with Mrs. Almazan</i>

8
00:00:15,167 --> 00:00:17,200
<i>and he harbors a grudge
against your fathers,</i>

9
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:19,100
<i>but that doesn't mean
he's the killer.</i>

10
00:00:19,100 --> 00:00:21,133
<i>We're going to look for him,
Mr. Almazan.</i>

11
00:00:21,133 --> 00:00:24,200
<i>And Roi will go to jail
for abducting your sister</i>

12
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:25,533
<i> and for what he did to Kiko.</i>

13
00:00:25,533 --> 00:00:26,867
<i> - I'll go with you too!
- No!</i>

14
00:00:26,867 --> 00:00:28,467
<i>You and Luna check
on Mom at our house.</i>

15
00:00:28,467 --> 00:00:29,667
<i> No matter what happens,</i>

16
00:00:29,667 --> 00:00:31,667
<i>make sure that Mom
is safe, okay?</i>

17
00:00:31,667 --> 00:00:33,067
<i>Thank you so much
for helping us out.</i>

18
00:00:33,067 --> 00:00:35,567
<i> You should be apologizing
to the Almazans.</i>

19
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,900
<i> Because you brought
Jade here.</i>

20
00:00:37,900 --> 00:00:40,133
<i> Frida, I love you so much.</i>

21
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:43,067
<i> I'd die if I can't have you!</i>

22
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:45,600
<i> Help!</i>

23
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:54,133
<i> Stop being stubborn, Jade.</i>

24
00:00:54,667 --> 00:00:56,500
<i> You look like your mother,
you know.</i>

25
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:58,100
<i> Such a creep!</i>

26
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,667
<i> You're so shameless!</i>

27
00:01:09,233 --> 00:01:11,133
[VOICE PROMPT]<i> ...be reached.
</i> Please try again later.

28
00:01:11,133 --> 00:01:14,633
Roi... [SIGHS]
I can't get ahold of him.

29
00:01:14,633 --> 00:01:16,733
[VOICE PROMPT]<i> This subscriber
</i> cannot be reached.

30
00:01:16,733 --> 00:01:18,533
<i> - Please try again later.
</i>- [SIGHS]

31
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:24,133
- [MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [LUNA SNIFFLES, SOBS]

32
00:01:25,967 --> 00:01:29,967
Why can't our family
ever catch a break?

33
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,067
Why are we being punished
like this?

34
00:01:35,667 --> 00:01:36,667
Luna...

35
00:01:38,267 --> 00:01:39,933
- That's enough.
- No.

36
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:44,533
Justin, are we bad people?

37
00:01:45,033 --> 00:01:46,800
Have we done anything wrong?

38
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:51,767
- [PHONE BEEPING]
- Please pick up.

39
00:01:53,667 --> 00:01:57,200
[PHONE RINGING]

40
00:01:58,233 --> 00:01:59,267
Martin.

41
00:01:59,967 --> 00:02:02,133
That's Martin?
Put him on speaker.

42
00:02:02,767 --> 00:02:03,767
[MARTIN] Hello, Luna?

43
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:05,567
<i> How are things there?</i>

44
00:02:05,567 --> 00:02:08,067
Martin, how about Jade?
Have you found her?

45
00:02:09,767 --> 00:02:10,867
Not yet, Justin.

46
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,567
They're still searching.

47
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,600
- I'll go there.
- Me too. I'll go.

48
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:16,800
<i> No need.</i>

49
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:21,000
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

50
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,633
<i>The police
also sent me home.</i>

51
00:02:24,833 --> 00:02:25,967
That's it?

52
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:30,100
This is Jade we're
talking about here.

53
00:02:30,833 --> 00:02:31,967
Our youngest.

54
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:34,567
I know, Luna.

55
00:02:35,933 --> 00:02:37,033
I know.

56
00:02:38,067 --> 00:02:40,633
But the police
won't stop searching.

57
00:02:40,633 --> 00:02:42,600
And we won't stop either.

58
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:44,833
<i> How about Mom? How is she?</i>

59
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:48,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:02:48,633 --> 00:02:49,633
Where's Mom?

61
00:02:51,067 --> 00:02:52,067
- Mom?
- Mom?

62
00:02:53,033 --> 00:02:53,900
[JUSTIN] Mom!

63
00:02:54,767 --> 00:02:56,067
- Mom!
- Mom!

64
00:02:56,067 --> 00:03:02,900
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

65
00:03:56,167 --> 00:03:57,833
- Mom!
- Mom! Mom!

66
00:03:58,767 --> 00:04:00,167
Mom, wait!

67
00:04:00,167 --> 00:04:01,167
Mom!

68
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:04,967
Mom! Mom!

69
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:07,700
Mom! Mom!

70
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:09,833
- Mom! Mom! Mom!
- No...

71
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:11,867
- You can't go. It's dangerous.
- Let me go.

72
00:04:11,867 --> 00:04:14,100
- I have to go.
- Mom, listen. Mom!

73
00:04:14,100 --> 00:04:17,033
- Mom, please listen!
- Let me go!

74
00:04:17,033 --> 00:04:18,833
We haven't found Jade yet.

75
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:20,800
We don't want you
to get hurt too.

76
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,133
Please, Mom.

77
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:26,933
I'm the one Roi wants.
Not Jade.

78
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:30,067
I have to find my daughter!

79
00:04:30,067 --> 00:04:31,800
- I have to find Jade.
- Mom, no.

80
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:33,200
- I have to find her.
- No, no, no.

81
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:36,267
- You can't.
- Mom, please. Please.

82
00:04:36,267 --> 00:04:39,300
[FRIDA] It's my fault. [SOBS]

83
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:41,033
- I have to find her.
- Mom. Mom.

84
00:04:41,033 --> 00:04:44,433
I'm the one Roi wants.
Not Jade.

85
00:04:44,433 --> 00:04:46,967
- Mom, it's dangerous.
- Mom. Mom.

86
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:49,267
I wonder what happened to them.

87
00:04:49,267 --> 00:04:50,867
I don't know.

88
00:04:50,867 --> 00:04:53,433
What if something else
had happened?

89
00:04:53,433 --> 00:04:57,367
What if the driver came back
and hurt them?

90
00:04:57,367 --> 00:04:59,267
What's going to happen now?
What if--

91
00:04:59,267 --> 00:05:01,200
Can you just shut up?!

92
00:05:01,233 --> 00:05:02,900
You're making me more nervous.

93
00:05:02,900 --> 00:05:05,100
Hey, hey, don't yell at me.

94
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,433
Who do you think you are?

95
00:05:06,433 --> 00:05:08,233
Why? Aren't you worried?

96
00:05:08,233 --> 00:05:09,900
Well, I'm worried
about my brother.

97
00:05:10,333 --> 00:05:12,933
How dare you tell me
to shut up!

98
00:05:12,933 --> 00:05:15,833
- Because you're so noisy!
- What? Bring it on!

99
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:17,767
- Whatever!
- I'm telling my brother!

100
00:05:17,767 --> 00:05:19,967
- Do it then!
- You bet I will!

101
00:05:19,967 --> 00:05:22,133
Please stop fighting.

102
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:23,933
- We're not fighting.
- We're not fighting.

103
00:05:24,967 --> 00:05:26,233
I'm not a warfreak, okay?

104
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,967
[SCOFFS]

105
00:05:30,233 --> 00:05:33,867
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

106
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:36,333
- This tension is killing me.
- [MIMICKING TRIXIE]

107
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,100
It's so hard not knowing
anything.

108
00:05:40,867 --> 00:05:42,833
Martin still hasn't
texted me back.

109
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:45,167
They wouldn't have time
to text back.

110
00:05:46,467 --> 00:05:49,500
- But... but...
- [CHESKA] What?

111
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:52,000
I know someone who might
know where Jade is.

112
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,933
- Who?
- Who?

113
00:05:53,933 --> 00:05:57,933
Then let's go see that person
so we can actually help.

114
00:05:57,933 --> 00:05:59,567
- Where are they?
- But what about the event?

115
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:01,500
Sir Martin told us
to monitor it.

116
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:02,833
Monette and Raphie
are here.

117
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:03,867
They're used to this.

118
00:06:03,867 --> 00:06:05,433
They know what they're
doing better than we do.

119
00:06:05,433 --> 00:06:06,500
Come on. Where are they?

120
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:08,367
Come on.

121
00:06:08,367 --> 00:06:11,600
Well? Should we go check?
Come on, let's go.

122
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,200
Let's go, Sari.

123
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,867
- You know where they are?
- Yeah.

124
00:06:14,867 --> 00:06:21,300
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

125
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:26,100
[GRUNTING]

126
00:06:32,367 --> 00:06:34,067
We got along fine, you know.

127
00:06:34,067 --> 00:06:40,167
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

128
00:06:40,167 --> 00:06:41,267
Honestly,

129
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:44,400
out of all of you siblings,

130
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,000
I like you best.

131
00:06:52,967 --> 00:06:55,400
You're nice and quiet.

132
00:06:56,967 --> 00:06:58,500
Unlike your sister, Luna.

133
00:07:00,167 --> 00:07:01,400
She's so arrogant.

134
00:07:08,167 --> 00:07:09,167
Too bad.

135
00:07:10,133 --> 00:07:12,000
If only you didn't snoop around.

136
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:18,833
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

137
00:07:19,567 --> 00:07:21,000
But don't worry.

138
00:07:22,467 --> 00:07:24,533
I just need to talk to Frida.

139
00:07:26,367 --> 00:07:29,567
She'll explain
everything to you.

140
00:07:32,133 --> 00:07:35,133
So you'll understand
why I did this.

141
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,500
And I love your mother.

142
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:44,000
I don't like seeing her hurt.

143
00:07:49,167 --> 00:07:52,300
I'd die...

144
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,600
and kill anyone...

145
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:59,000
...for her.

146
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:05,967
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

147
00:08:16,067 --> 00:08:17,167
[SARI] We're here.

148
00:08:18,667 --> 00:08:20,933
[TRIXIE] Here? Are you sure?

149
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:25,467
Didn't you say you know someone
who can help us locate Jade?

150
00:08:25,467 --> 00:08:28,000
Yes, that's why I brought you
to our house.

151
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,933
[CHESKA] Your house?

152
00:08:30,733 --> 00:08:33,000
What are we doing here?

153
00:08:35,300 --> 00:08:38,267
- [SHRIEKS, YELPS]
- Hey! Hey! Hey!

154
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:40,433
What's with the knife?
Give me that!

155
00:08:40,433 --> 00:08:42,467
I was going to peel
some coconuts.

156
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:46,000
[SARI] You're doing that
at this hour?

157
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:48,600
[BOTONG] Is there a specified
time to peel coconuts?

158
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,667
Uh...

159
00:08:49,667 --> 00:08:51,200
And who are these two?

160
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,500
Hey, careful.

161
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:56,567
Oh, these are Cheska
and Trixie, Grandpa.

162
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:58,133
You're too loud.

163
00:09:00,433 --> 00:09:03,200
G-Good evening.
I'm Cheska.

164
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,567
Hello. Trixie here.

165
00:09:04,567 --> 00:09:05,700
Good evening.

166
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,667
Uh, this is my grandpa.

167
00:09:08,667 --> 00:09:12,133
He can tell us where Jade is.

168
00:09:15,667 --> 00:09:17,000
How?

169
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:21,233
He's one of the most famous
and brilliant healers

170
00:09:21,233 --> 00:09:23,300
and fortune tellers
on this island.

171
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:25,200
- Fortune teller?
- [CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

172
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,700
- [PHONE CAMERA CLICKS]
- Hey. What's that? Hm?

173
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:34,667
Thank goodness the music fest
ended without a hitch

174
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:36,267
and everyone had fun!

175
00:09:36,267 --> 00:09:39,167
There's no doubt that
our event was a success,

176
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:41,367
so congratulations, sirs!

177
00:09:43,133 --> 00:09:46,467
I'd like to thank you,
Raphie, and Monette.

178
00:09:46,467 --> 00:09:50,400
We're extremely grateful
that we can rely on you.

179
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:52,067
Don't mention it, sir.

180
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:56,467
If only Monette and I could do
anything to ease your worries,

181
00:09:56,467 --> 00:09:58,033
we'd have done it already

182
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:02,633
I wonder how Miss Jade is doing.

183
00:10:02,633 --> 00:10:03,700
[PHONE CHIMES]

184
00:10:08,167 --> 00:10:09,533
Come on, hurry up!

185
00:10:10,667 --> 00:10:11,667
Get out of here.

186
00:10:13,567 --> 00:10:17,500
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

187
00:10:17,500 --> 00:10:21,767
Well? Didn't I tell you
I'm a good boy?

188
00:10:21,767 --> 00:10:23,500
Shut up.

189
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:28,200
You should've believed me
when I said I was innocent.

190
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:31,633
You don't even have evidence
to prove I stole the car.

191
00:10:31,633 --> 00:10:32,633
Yeah, yeah.

192
00:10:32,633 --> 00:10:36,067
Just sign here.
After that, you can leave.

193
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:41,800
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

194
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:43,133
I'll get going now.

195
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:46,633
It's payback time.

196
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:51,733
No updates from the police yet,

197
00:10:51,733 --> 00:10:54,233
but I know they're doing
everything they can.

198
00:10:54,233 --> 00:10:56,100
You heard that, Kiko?

199
00:10:56,100 --> 00:10:58,200
The police are doing their best.

200
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:00,333
They won't abandon Jade
so you can calm down now.

201
00:11:00,333 --> 00:11:02,100
[KIKO] I can't do that, Gio.

202
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:04,367
I was with Jade
when she was abducted.

203
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:06,633
If only I had managed
to fight back--

204
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:08,133
[RAPHIE] Kiko, you were
knocked unconscious.

205
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:09,433
That isn't an excuse, Raphie.

206
00:11:09,433 --> 00:11:13,667
Had I not been knocked out,
Roi couldn't have taken Jade.

207
00:11:13,667 --> 00:11:15,567
This isn't your fault, Kiko.

208
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:17,900
Don't blame yourself.

209
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:24,800
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

210
00:11:27,667 --> 00:11:30,367
[CLEARS THROAT]
I think it's time to rest.

211
00:11:30,367 --> 00:11:32,433
Maybe we should call it a night.

212
00:11:32,433 --> 00:11:35,167
I'm sure Sir Henry will have
an update for us tomorrow.

213
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:39,200
Wait, where's Trixie? Has she
returned from the event?

214
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,900
Oh, I didn't get to
talk to her all night,

215
00:11:41,933 --> 00:11:46,567
but I saw her leave
with Miss Cheska and Sari.

216
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:49,867
Cheska's not back either?

217
00:11:49,867 --> 00:11:56,800
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:12:11,933 --> 00:12:13,633
- What's he doing?
- Shh!

219
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:16,800
Just wait. Don't make a noise.

220
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:20,267
Yeah, shut up.
You might disturb him.

221
00:12:20,267 --> 00:12:21,867
Let him do his thing.

222
00:12:22,967 --> 00:12:24,400
I was just asking.

223
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:34,467
What's that candle for?

224
00:12:34,467 --> 00:12:35,500
Shh!

225
00:12:40,667 --> 00:12:42,400
[BOTONG] There is...

226
00:12:43,733 --> 00:12:45,767
...a cool breeze.

227
00:12:45,767 --> 00:12:47,867
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

228
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:54,733
[WIND HOWLING]

229
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:58,000
You know what?
This is crazy. I'm going home.

230
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,667
Shh!

231
00:12:59,667 --> 00:13:02,967
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

232
00:13:02,967 --> 00:13:08,800
There's an isolated house...

233
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:11,300
...on an island.

234
00:13:12,533 --> 00:13:15,000
[CANDLE WAX
DRIPPING ON WATER]

235
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,600
[CHESKA WHISPERING]
Guys, what's going on?

236
00:13:18,633 --> 00:13:23,600
The old house on that island...

237
00:13:24,933 --> 00:13:30,767
...stands in the middle
of two palm trees.

238
00:13:36,767 --> 00:13:39,567
That's where they took
the woman.

239
00:13:39,567 --> 00:13:46,533
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

240
00:13:46,533 --> 00:13:47,733
[BLOWS]

241
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:50,767
- [BOTONG HUFFS]
- [SARI GASPS]

242
00:13:50,767 --> 00:13:52,967
Grandpa, are you alright?

243
00:13:53,767 --> 00:13:56,467
Y-Yeah, I'm fine.

244
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:57,700
I'm fine.

245
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:04,467
Did you hear what Grandpa said?

246
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:06,867
Mm-hmm.

247
00:14:06,867 --> 00:14:09,433
In a house...

248
00:14:10,467 --> 00:14:12,033
in the middle of an island,

249
00:14:13,333 --> 00:14:17,967
sandwiched between
two palm trees.

250
00:14:22,567 --> 00:14:23,933
Nice one, Grandpa.

251
00:14:25,433 --> 00:14:26,467
So cool

252
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:28,700
- Are you okay, Grandpa?
- Yeah.

253
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:34,467
Hey, they're here.

254
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:39,733
Would it kill you to update us?
You had us worried sick!

255
00:14:39,733 --> 00:14:41,433
I'm sorry, Martin.

256
00:14:41,433 --> 00:14:43,133
- [MARTIN HUFFS]
- There was no signal there.

257
00:14:44,567 --> 00:14:46,600
Honestly, I shouldn't
have gone with them.

258
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:49,400
Yeah, right.
You believed it, too.

259
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:50,700
Excuse me?

260
00:14:50,700 --> 00:14:52,300
Where were you anyway?

261
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:56,700
We went to Sari's house.

262
00:14:56,700 --> 00:14:58,033
Sari's house?

263
00:14:58,833 --> 00:15:01,300
Well, Sari said...

264
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:07,300
she knew someone who could
help us locate Jade.

265
00:15:07,333 --> 00:15:11,567
I couldn't just pass that up.
I want to help too.

266
00:15:11,567 --> 00:15:13,167
Who was it?

267
00:15:13,167 --> 00:15:15,600
Sari's grandfather
happens to be...

268
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:17,467
- ...a fortune teller.
- What did he say?

269
00:15:17,467 --> 00:15:22,633
He said there's a house
on an island...

270
00:15:22,633 --> 00:15:25,533
...sandwiched between
two palm trees.

271
00:15:25,533 --> 00:15:27,267
That's where Jade is.

272
00:15:27,267 --> 00:15:29,833
But there's so many houses
like that on this island!

273
00:15:29,833 --> 00:15:31,167
[CHESKA] Well...

274
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:33,867
Sari said her grandpa
is a famous fortune teller.

275
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:37,533
Look, don't just
believe Sari, okay?

276
00:15:37,567 --> 00:15:39,367
Because if you...

277
00:15:39,367 --> 00:15:42,733
If you disappear too,
I'm going to lose my mind!

278
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:45,833
- Martin...
- Go to sleep!

279
00:15:46,667 --> 00:15:47,833
- Bro.
- What?

280
00:15:47,833 --> 00:15:50,400
- I took a video. Look.
- Forget it. Get some rest.

281
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:52,400
Just look at it, bro.

282
00:15:53,433 --> 00:15:54,567
You aren't curious?

283
00:15:56,233 --> 00:16:02,700
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

284
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:05,567
Not too long after I was
hired as your driver,

285
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:08,467
my mother got sick.

286
00:16:10,567 --> 00:16:15,833
Not one hospital
wanted to accept her.

287
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:20,233
But Frida...

288
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:24,400
She did everything...

289
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:28,367
to have my mother treated.

290
00:16:30,700 --> 00:16:34,600
She wasn't just pretty.

291
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:38,300
She has a very good heart, too.

292
00:16:42,833 --> 00:16:44,600
Mama eventually died.

293
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:50,767
But that only...

294
00:16:52,933 --> 00:16:54,667
...revived my weary heart.

295
00:16:55,733 --> 00:16:57,433
I fell in love with Frida.

296
00:17:00,533 --> 00:17:04,433
I promised myself
that no matter what happens...

297
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:06,933
I will protect her.

298
00:17:06,933 --> 00:17:13,867
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

299
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:24,367
I never thought ill of Roi

300
00:17:24,367 --> 00:17:27,533
because he's been with us
for many years!

301
00:17:27,533 --> 00:17:30,933
[LUNA] Then why are you saying
he might've killed Dad?

302
00:17:30,933 --> 00:17:34,400
Because he told me
to go home that day.

303
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:37,267
He said he'd
take care of things, so...

304
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:39,833
I didn't know what he'd do!

305
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:44,467
- Ma.
- Leon...

306
00:17:44,467 --> 00:17:46,367
Are there any updates?

307
00:17:46,367 --> 00:17:50,933
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

308
00:17:50,967 --> 00:17:52,433
Oh my god...

309
00:17:52,433 --> 00:17:54,933
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

310
00:17:55,833 --> 00:17:57,600
Jade...

311
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:59,933
Where could Jade be?

312
00:17:59,933 --> 00:18:01,600
Where is Jade?

313
00:18:02,467 --> 00:18:05,567
"Sir, we're all still awake.
Just call if you have updates."

314
00:18:16,033 --> 00:18:17,267
[PHONE CHIMES]

315
00:18:18,967 --> 00:18:20,533
What did they say?

316
00:18:22,767 --> 00:18:24,833
"We're still doing our rounds."

317
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:28,700
Still no update.

318
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:29,700
Tsk!

319
00:18:30,867 --> 00:18:32,733
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

320
00:18:34,700 --> 00:18:36,500
I'm sorry, Fred.

321
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:39,667
I'm so sorry.

322
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:44,933
Mom, go get some rest first.

323
00:18:45,767 --> 00:18:47,800
We'll monitor the search.

324
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:52,967
As if I'd get a wink of sleep
in this situation.

325
00:18:57,900 --> 00:19:04,867
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

326
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:09,400
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

327
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:11,000
[HENRI] With the new evidence

328
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:14,333
and with Mrs. Almazan's
new statement,

329
00:19:14,333 --> 00:19:18,800
it's become clearer that Roi was
at the crime scene at that time.

330
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:23,500
That means he's now a suspect
in your fathers' deaths.

331
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:26,600
Will our fathers' case
be reopened?

332
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:29,733
That's right.

333
00:19:29,733 --> 00:19:36,500
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

334
00:19:41,767 --> 00:19:48,700
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

335
00:20:02,333 --> 00:20:09,000
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

336
00:20:11,300 --> 00:20:18,267
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

337
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:37,267
[DARK MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

338
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:47,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

339
00:20:47,100 --> 00:20:48,700
It's devastating if it's true.

340
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:51,367
It would mean Papa
just got caught up

341
00:20:51,367 --> 00:20:52,667
in that guy's obsession.

342
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:55,367
There's just one thing
that doesn't make sense.

343
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:56,933
What?

344
00:20:57,667 --> 00:20:59,933
Why did Papa
bring a gun that day?

345
00:20:59,933 --> 00:21:03,333
They said it was Papa's gun
that was used, right?

346
00:21:03,333 --> 00:21:05,500
And according to
the witnesses' testimonies,

347
00:21:05,500 --> 00:21:07,067
Papa was furious.

348
00:21:07,067 --> 00:21:09,067
So how did he get caught up
in Roi's obsession?

349
00:21:09,833 --> 00:21:11,567
We can't answer that.

350
00:21:11,567 --> 00:21:13,667
We don't know
what really happened.

351
00:21:13,667 --> 00:21:14,967
After being away from home
for so long,

352
00:21:14,967 --> 00:21:17,400
there's so much about Papa and
Uncle Fred we no longer know.

353
00:21:18,733 --> 00:21:20,933
But if Roi really
was the murderer...

354
00:21:22,033 --> 00:21:24,533
that would mean Papa and
Uncle Fred's friendship

355
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:25,833
was real.

356
00:21:26,567 --> 00:21:29,700
And this ongoing beef we have
with the Almazans...

357
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,733
I feel like we really
should end it.

358
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:36,967
Jade's life is still in danger.

359
00:21:36,967 --> 00:21:40,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

360
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:43,967
Shouldn't we patch things up
with the Almazans for real?

361
00:21:49,733 --> 00:21:50,967
The more time passes,

362
00:21:50,967 --> 00:21:53,100
the more I can't stop thinking
about all sorts of things.

363
00:21:53,100 --> 00:21:55,067
Stay strong, Mom.

364
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,833
Have they still not called
or sent any updates?

365
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:01,600
[FRIDA SIGHS]

366
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:07,933
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:22:09,433 --> 00:22:10,400
Edward.

368
00:22:10,867 --> 00:22:12,833
- Edward.
- Edward.

369
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:18,967
I have good news.

370
00:22:18,967 --> 00:22:25,867
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

371
00:22:31,467 --> 00:22:37,600
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

372
00:22:46,667 --> 00:22:48,933
[KIKO] I hope Jade makes it
through all of this.

373
00:22:49,567 --> 00:22:51,933
<i>I hope we don't go through
any more pain.</i>

374
00:22:51,933 --> 00:22:58,000
[STIRRING MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

375
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:01,333
<i>Roi must've used the car to go
to one of the islands here.</i>

376
00:23:01,333 --> 00:23:03,267
<i>We'll go with you,
wherever it is.</i>

377
00:23:03,267 --> 00:23:05,667
<i>Did you know Mom and Dad
have already separated?</i>

378
00:23:05,667 --> 00:23:07,033
<i> She wanted to leave.</i>

379
00:23:07,033 --> 00:23:09,100
<i> No one's leaving!</i>

380
00:23:09,100 --> 00:23:11,267
<i> Where's Jade?
Where's my daughter?</i>

381
00:23:11,267 --> 00:23:13,033
<i>I'll send you the place
where we'll meet.</i>

382
00:23:13,033 --> 00:23:14,033
<i> Don't try to fool me.</i>

383
00:23:14,033 --> 00:23:16,067
<i>You can't go there alone,
Mrs. Almazan.</i>

384
00:23:16,067 --> 00:23:17,500
<i> He'll kill my daughter</i>

385
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:19,200
<i>if he finds out I brought
cops with me.</i>

386
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,333
<i> How about we follow them?</i>

387
00:23:20,333 --> 00:23:22,000
<i> Kiko, we can't.</i>

388
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,367
<i> So we'll just wait?</i>

389
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:25,367
<i> We can't just sit back
and do nothing.</i>

